Token Revocation Example

To disable an access or refresh token, you can revoke it by making a POST request to the token revocation URL with the following parameters:

token - the access token or refresh token to revoke

token_type_hint (optional) - the token parameter's type‚Äîeither access_token or refresh_token
When you revoke a token, any active access or refresh tokens associated with that authorization will be revoked, regardless of the token and token_type_hint values you pass in.
